<HL>
   Lifetime Corp. Buys Markka
</HL>
<DATE>
06/14/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B5
</SO>
<CO>
   LFT
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   BOSTON -- Lifetime Corp. bought Markka Healthcare Inc. of
Atlanta for about $12 million, with $1.1 million of the
purchase price contingent upon Markka's revenue for the
following 12 months.
   Markka, a provider of infusion therapy and respiratory
devices, had annual revenue of about $6 million in 1989.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Lifetime, a provider of home health-care personnel, said
about $4 million of the total purchase price may be paid in
company stock.
</TEXT>
